Southern Poverty Law Center in February filed a lawsuit against Georgia Department of Corrections officials on behalf of transgender inmate Ashley Diamond  . 
  Diamond identifies as a female and has been on hormone therapy since she was 17 . 
  The lawsuit says prison officials have failed to provide adequate treatment for Diamond's gender dysphoria . 
  The Eighth Amendment of the U . 
 S . 
  Constitution requires officials to treat an inmate's gender identity condition just as they would treat any other medical or mental health condition  . 
 